Problem statement: 
	create a script that can encrypt a given file and create a qr code for it. 
	The user would need to password to read the file post scanning the QRcode. 

Here's what the script is intended to do upon completion: 

Read all pdf files in a folder
For each file in folder:
	check if file is encrypted
	If not encrypt the file. 
	Rename the file and append the file name with  "_encrypted". 
For all encrypted files
	Upload file to cloud
	Generate a sahred link 
	Append the link to dictionary (key is the file name: value is the shared link)
For each item in dictionary:
	create QR Code 
	Rename QR code to reflect the name of the file
